 <p>
  <strong>
   Xbox Game Pass
  </strong>
  subscribers can look forward to two more day-one Game Pass drops in
  <em>
   Voidtrain
  </em>
  and
  <em>
   Lost in Random: The Eternal Die
  </em>
  next year. The Opening Night Live event at Gamescom 2024 may be over, but Xbox continues to show off more upcoming titles, revealing
  <em>
   Revenge of the Savage Planet
  </em>
  , gameplay of day-one Xbox Game Pass title
  <em>
   Atomfall
  </em>
  , and a deep dive into
  <em>
   Starfield
  </em>
  's imminent
  <em>
   Shattered Space
  </em>
  DLC.
 </p>
 <!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. -->
 <!-- Repeatable debug data: {"injection":"none","adPosition":1,"startingPoint":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":1,"ruleCount":900,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"stopAds":null,"actualCount":411} -->
 <p>
  Xbox already has an immense list of titles lined up for 2025, many of which are first-party. Obsidian Entertainment's
  <em>
   Avowed,
  </em>
  which was originally slated for release this year, is coming on February 11.
  <em>
   Doom: The Dark Ages
  </em>
  ,
  <em>
   South of Midnight
  </em>
  , and
  <em>
   Fable
  </em>
  are also aiming to be 2025 day-one Game Pass releases. Beyond that, several big third-party titles are picking up the slack, such as
  <em>
   Expedition 33
  </em>
  ,
  <em>
   Sniper Elite: Resistance
  </em>
  ,
  <em>
   Wuchang: Fallen Feathers,
  </em>
  and more, rounding out an incredible-looking 2025 for Game Pass users.
 </p>
 <!-- Repeatable debug data: {"injection":"before","adPosition":1,"startingPoint":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":1,"nbrPlacementsScanned":1,"ruleCount":900,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"stopAds":null,"isEarlyInjection":false,"actualCount":940} -->
