 <p>
  Despite all this, it seems Xbox still has more up its sleeve for Game Pass in 2025. During its second-day Gamescom livestream, Xbox confirmed two more titles coming day-one to Game Pass next year. An isometric,
  <em>
   Diablo
  </em>
  -like action twist on 2021's
  <em>
   Coraline
  </em>
  -inspired EA Originals adventure game,
  <em>
   Lost in Random: The Eternal Die
  </em>
  was unveiled and confirmed as a Game Pass release during the livestream. The second game, a survival title named
  <em>
   Voidtrain
  </em>
  , will see players building and customizing their own train that they can use to embark on a journey to explore a surreal and mysterious void.
 </p>
