  <em>
   Fallout 76
  </em>
  's creative director, Jonathan Rush, revealed a teaser trailer, which featured locations that were filled with Ultracite, hence the name Gleaming Depths. With Ultracite being a rare radioactive crystal residing in the depths of Appalachia, this presents the perfect opportunity for the next update to focus on a map location that is in need of some love: the Ash Heap. The mines of
  <em>
   Fallout 76
  </em>
  are filled with mysteries, and the Ash Heap could finally be explored to its full extent.
 </p>
