 <p>
  Much of the area's smoky atmosphere comes from the mines that lie underneath the land. It is believed that there are non-stop fires raging in the tunnels below, but there hasn't been any real confirmation about what lies beneath the Ash Heap's surface. Since there are mines, there is bound to be some sort of precious resource, and it wouldn't be too wild to assume that this resource is Ultracite. This resource is all over Appalachia, and the footage Rush revealed for Gleaming Depths showcasing an ample amount of Ultracite could be teasing what is hiding underneath the Ash Heap. Ultracite is a powerful component, and it would make since that there is a substantial supply buried under the location's surface.
 </p>
